A quick look to some of the manifestation on the Internationale women&#8217;s rights fight day.

While hundreds of thousands of people have marched around the world, shouting and demanding women&#8217;s just right to exist in safety, with dignity and freedom, in some countries they don&#8217;t even have the right to speak. To work as they wish, to move around, to live free from fear and tears.

That&#8217;s why we have to fight. Stay aware, point up !

# Turkey {.wp-block-heading}<figure class="wp-block-video"><video controls src="http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/8march-Turquie2024-9655881.mp4"></video></figure> 

&#8220;&#8221;Turkish police have intervened in the Istanbul University students’ march held for International Women’s Day allegedly over a banner reading “LGBTIQ+,” and detained many of them. The police attacked the students coming out of the faculty gate and detained them with methods amounting to torture.&#8221;&#8221; https://www.youtube.com/embed/p16JgZQzjZA

[İstanbul Üniversitesi&#8217;nde 8 Mart Yürüyüşü&#8217;ne polis saldırısı][1]

&#8220;&#8221;According to [We Will Stop Femicide,][2] a prominent activist group in Turkey, 338 women have been murdered since March 2023, and 248 died under suspicious circumstances.&#8221;&#8221;

