&#8220;While some are celebrating historic steps taken in countries like Mexico, which is [slated to elect a woman as president][10] for the first time, others are railing against potential rollbacks on rights they’ve long fought for in places like Argentina with the arrival of [far-right President Javier Milei][11]. (…) [Since taking office in December][12],  
